{"_type":"issue","id":"SWP-9cu","title":"Add timeout protection to direct LLM mode","description":"Skill mode respects execution.timeout but the direct LLM path in adapter.py calls _call_llm() with no timeout. A hung Anthropic API call blocks the entire job indefinitely. Should wrap the API call with a timeout matching the configured execution.timeout. Found in PR #30 review.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"bot@ambient-code.local","created_at":"2026-05-27T14:48:03Z","created_by":"Ambient Code Bot","updated_at":"2026-05-27T14:48:03Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"SWP-g25","title":"Handle non-text LLM response content blocks","description":"adapter.py checks response.content is non-empty but assumes response.content[0].text exists. A tool-use or non-text content block would crash. Should validate the content block type before accessing .text. Found in PR #30 review.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"bot@ambient-code.local","created_at":"2026-05-27T14:48:10Z","created_by":"Ambient Code Bot","updated_at":"2026-05-27T14:48:10Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"SWP-atg","title":"Surface judge scoring failures in results","description":"_load_judges_and_score() catches all exceptions and returns {}. Users cannot distinguish 'no judges configured' from 'judges crashed'. Should log at ERROR level and include scoring error in results metadata. Found in PR #30 review.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"bot@ambient-code.local","created_at":"2026-05-27T14:48:06Z","created_by":"Ambient Code Bot","updated_at":"2026-05-27T14:48:06Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"SWP-lcj","title":"Fix aggregate exit code logic in EvalHub adapter","description":"adapter.py uses max(..., key=abs) for aggregate exit_code across runs. This treats exit codes as magnitudes — [0, 0, -1] yields -1, which is semantically wrong. Exit codes are status indicators. Should use first-failure or any-failure-means-1 pattern. Found in PR #30 review.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"bot@ambient-code.local","created_at":"2026-05-27T14:47:57Z","created_by":"Ambient Code Bot","updated_at":"2026-05-27T14:47:57Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
